title.narrative: DRR AND EMERGENCY IN SOCIAL WELFARE SYS.

description.narrative: Social welfare system is strengthened for DRR and emergency response., which contributes to Child Protection And Emergencies, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Vulnerable children and their families are adequately supported so that their resilience to poverty and external shocks is increased and they live in a safe, non-violent family or family-like environment

title.narrative: Social welfare system is strengthened for DRR and emergency response.

description.narrative: Capacities of the national child protection system and migration management have been further supported to ensure adequate protection of refugee/migrant children and comprehensive fulfilment of their child rights in line with the CRC. As mixed migration flows continued, UNICEF focused on improving sustainability of capacity-building efforts, improving awareness, identification and response for the most vulnerable groups who have been less visible (unaccompanied or separated girls, boys survivors of sexual violence, children at risk of substance abuse), mainstreaming GBV and sexual exploitation and abuse prevention and response in the sector, as well as maintaining a strategic monitoring presence in the field. | Status:Met | As-of Date:18/12/2020
